issue.title: NestedComponent - error handling
issue.body:
**OpenUI5 version:**
1.108
**Browser/version (+device/version):**
Chrome

**URL (minimal example if possible):**
https://sdk.openui5.org/entity/sap.ui.core.routing.Router/sample/sap.ui.core.sample.RoutingNestedComponent/code
https://sdk.openui5.org/topic/fb19f501b16e4e4991eb6a017770945b

**What is the expected result and what happens instead?**
We have an app with more than 15 NestedComponents. The setup of the app with its NestedComponents is identical to the recommendations in the links above. Loading and navigation between the components work fine.

Now, we are encountering an issue when the user's session expires, and the user attempts to navigate to a NestedComponent that was not loaded in his/her active session before. In the browser console, I see an error from 'sap.ui.core' with a 'ModuleError' exception: 'ModuleError: failed to load '.. URL of the NestedComponent ...' from '.. URL of the current component ..'.

I would like to catch this exception or attach some kind of event handler to UIComponent, Router, or whatever is necessary so that we can inform the user that something went wrong.

Currently, nothing happens when the user tries to navigate to the NestedComponent, because UI5 just throws the exception.

**Any other information? (attach screenshot if possible)**
![image](https://github.com/SAP/openui5/assets/102368386/804606d1-1aa4-4274-80b4-c134e901d329)

Unfortunately, I couldn't find any information about error handling for NestedComponents on sdk.openui5, and I'm seeking help on this topic because it's not clear whether this is a missing functionality of UI5.

Regards
TheNorthBridge

comment.body:
Hello @TheNorthBridge 
Thank you for sharing your enhancement proposal. I've created an internal incident 2370131436. The status of the issue will be updated here in GitHub.

First of all, please be informed that our samples are just for an illustration of the API, not for direct usage in an application.
In your description, I do not see any specific control issue reported. Only a screenshot of a console error is not enough as a description of an issue. 
Please, analyse in details the problem from application side and if you find a OpenUI5 control related issue or an enhancement needed, please describe it in details, in order to be able to support you.

issue.title: Type issue due to sap.m.WizardStep events jsDoc being too unspecific
issue.body:
The API doc for [sap.m.WizardStep events](https://sdk.openui5.org/api/sap.m.WizardStep#events/Summary) is quite unspecific as the `getParameters` method of each event just returns type object.
I would have expected something more specific e.g. like the [selectionChange event of sap.m.ListBase](https://sdk.openui5.org/api/sap.m.ListBase#events/selectionChange) where the parameters are explicitly listed.

Because of that the type `WizardStep$CompleteEventParameters` from `sap.m.d.ts` that is generated based on the API doc currently throws an error for 

```
onStepCompleted (event: WizardStep$CompleteEvent) {
    let currentStepId = event.getParameter("id"); // <-- Argument of type 'string' is not assignable to parameter of type 'never'
    [...]
}
```

although `id` is in fact a valid parameter of the complete event of a wizard step.

comment.body:
Hey @niyap,

I'm afraid that's not correct. The complete event of a WizardStep as of now offers the parameter `id` (e.g. in UI5 version 1.119.2) that contains the id of the WizardStep that triggered the complete event (so same as `event.getSource().getId()`)

Chrome console:
![image](https://github.com/SAP/openui5/assets/73878785/412ae943-8aa8-4141-b3d6-502fe61e081f)

I think same is true for `activate`. 

So in case you adjust the return type of `getParameters` in the documentation to not return anything (which is also fine for me) you should as well adjust the actual implementation to not offer the parameters as shown in the screenshot above.

Cheers
Dominik

issue.title: Enhancement: sap.m.Text should have a font-style option like italic, underscore
issue.body:
OpenUI5 version: 1.108.13

I believe it would be nice to have a property to render all text of a sap.m.Text as italic, bold, underline,... 

I understand that the Text control should be simple and that there are options with css and addClass and other controls that allow more flexibility. Still, it is simple, I do not see a downside and it might come handy.

My use case: I have a sap.ui.table.Table and data is shown in a sap.m.Text controls. The text property is bound to the row/column value and if that is null, it should use the string `<null>` instead. Rendered in italic via another bound property.

issue.title: Enhancement: sap.m.Text should have a font-style option like italic, underscore
issue.body:

I believe it would be nice to have a property to render all text of a sap.m.Text as italic, bold, underline,... 

I understand that the Text control should be simple and that there are options with css and addClass and other controls that allow more flexibility. Still, it is simple, I do not see a downside and it might come handy.

My use case: I have a sap.ui.table.Table and data is shown in a sap.m.Text controls. The text property is bound to the row/column value and if that is null, it should use the string `<null>` instead. Rendered in italic via another bound property.

comment.body:
Hello @wernerdaehn,

After request to our designers for adding possibility to add styles to the sap.m.Text via the API it was rejected.

The motivation is:
We use different text stylings for ACC reasons and visual hierarchy or to have a distinction between different elements.
Offering API to change styles is something we do not recommend. 
The features requested can be achieved with custom CSS that is not complex (setting "italic" or "bold" in table ) and there is low risk of additional issues.

Best Regards,
Lidiya

issue.title: Partial select for tree table
issue.body:
OpenUI5 version:
SAP UI5 version: "1.115.1"

Steps to reproduce the problem:
1. Expand a parent row of a tree table with children.
2. Select a child of a parent row in a tree table.
3. Collapse the child rows so only the parent row is visible.
4. There is no indication that the child inside the parent node is selected.

What is the expected result?
I expect the parent row to be partially selected. The desired behaviour can be observed when using sap.m.Checkbox ([Sample: Tri-State Check Box](https://sapui5.hana.ondemand.com/#/entity/sap.m.CheckBox/sample/sap.m.sample.CheckBoxTriState))

What happens instead?
Only the child row is selected. The selection does not have an effect on the parent row selection.
